Package org.daiitech.naftah.builtin.time

Interface ArabicTemporalPoint

All Superinterfaces:
ArabicTemporal
All Known Implementing Classes:
ArabicDate, ArabicDateTime, ArabicTime
public sealed interface ArabicTemporalPoint extends ArabicTemporal permits ArabicTime, ArabicDate, ArabicDateTime
Marker interface representing an Arabic temporal point.

A temporal point represents a specific position on the time-line (such as a date, time, or date-time) with an Arabic textual representation.

This sealed interface provides a common abstraction for all Arabic-aware temporal points and allows access to their underlying Temporal representation.

The following implementations are permitted:

  • ArabicTime – a time-only temporal point
  • ArabicDate – a date-only temporal point
  • ArabicDateTime – a combined date and time temporal point

Author:
Chakib Daii
